    <section>
      <!--h1-->
      <title>About the Anti-XSS Test Harness</title>
      <content>
        <para>
          The Anti-XSS Test Harness is a console application that automates validation and performance tests for the Anti-XSS Library.
        </para>
        <para>
          <link xlink:href="f0bf6d6d-b437-4c9f-811f-6f23aad7654f">XSS Validation Test Bench</link> demonstrates the successful blocking of cross-site scripts. These tests use XSS exploits as attack vectors for testing. Attack vectors are read from a text file and then encoded output is stored in an output file.
        </para>
        <para>
          <link xlink:href="5b080580-36ad-4715-9c61-952509070730">Performance Test Bench</link> benchmarks the performance of the AntiXss.HtmlEncoding method of the Anti-XSS library against the .NET HttpUtility.HtmlEncode encoding method. Performance results are stored in an output file.
        </para>
      </content>
    </section>

